{"cursor":"8647","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox musical artist\n| name = Black Roots image = Black Roots.jpg caption = image_size = background =\n| group_or_band origin = Bristol, England, UK genre = Reggae years_active =\n| since 1979 label = Nubian Records (some product licensed and released via\n| Kick, BBC Records and Tapes, Makasound/Soundicate, Bristol Archive Records and\n| Sugar Shack Records) website = https://www.facebook.com/blackrootsreggae\n| current_members = Errol Brown Charles Bryan aka Delroy O'Gilvie Kondwani Ngozi Jabulani Ngozi Cordell Francis Carlton Smith\n| past_members = Errol Brown Charles Bryan aka Delroy O'Gilvie Kondwani Ngozi Jabulani Ngozi Cordell Francis Trevor\n| Seivwright Derrick King Carlton Smith\n}} 'Black Roots' are a roots reggae band from the St. Paul's area of Bristol,\nEngland formed in 1979. Larkin, Colin (1998) The Virgin\nEncyclopedia of Reggae, Virgin Books, ISBN 0-7535-0242-9, p.27-28 Whiteley, Sheila, Bennett, Andy, & Hawkins, Stan (2005) Music,\nSpace and Place: popular music and cultural identity, Ashgate Publishing, ISBN\n978-0-7546-5574-9, p.73-74 They toured extensively in the UK and Europe in\nthe 1980s and early 1990s releasing several albums and singles during that time\nbefore disappearing from the music scene for about 10 years. Their comeback\nbegan when Soundicate/Makasound, a record label in France, released an album in\n2004 and followed it up with another in 2007 (both were compilations made up\nfrom their extensive back catalogue). In December 2010 they performed their\nfirst live show for some 20 years at the Trinity Hall in Bristol and since then\nthey have been active once again playing selected live dates, writing, composing\nand arranging songs and music, and releasing their first studio album in over 20\nyears in September 2012 entitled 'On The Ground'. More reissues and new material\nreleases are planned.\n","linknr":145,"url":"Black_Roots_(band)","recorded":13750813